The article urges residents in Texas to take precautions as Hurricane Harvey approaches. It emphasizes the importance of heeding the warnings of local officials and complying with evacuation orders. Those who choose to ignore evacuation orders not only put themselves at risk, but also endanger the lives of first responders. The article advises those unable to evacuate to inform friends and family of their location. It also suggests visiting www.ready.gov to learn how to prepare for the storm and downloading the FEMA mobile app for access to emergency supplies and shelter information. The Federal Government, specifically FEMA, is working with state and local officials to coordinate preparation, response, and recovery efforts. Thomas P. Bossert serves as the Homeland Security Advisor to President Donald J. Trump.